RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb.

RAIN OF BLESSING raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. SHADY DAISY raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path, began a bid in upper stretch and improved position in the final furlong. BANK BUSTER bumped lightly with the horse to her inside at the start, settled in the middle of the pack through the opening stages, came around the bend in the three path and finished evenly. MY SONG AND MELODY led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and tired in the lane. TAIPANS CHERRYBOMB was bumped hard and blocked at the start, trailed the field through the opening quarter, raced in the three path around the turn and made no bid. MISS INEZ bumped mildly with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, raced at the back of the pack early, swung out to the four and five path coming around the turn and was empty in the lane.
